reviews.title: Sweet treat!
reviews.text:
We were looking to grab a bite on our way to Germany and wanted to treat the kids to something sweet.

Lovely location, view of the harbour and inviting decor. Staff were very friendly and accommodating.

Kids had the children's pancake which was good value, you can choose as many toppings as you like plus a gift at the end. It's a massive portion though, way too much to finish, even for my enthusiastic 5 year old.

I had the poffertjes, which I never tried before. Initially I loved them but they were very fatty. I don't mind fatty food but there were lumps of butter in the middle of the dish so in addition to the poffertjes and whopped cream it was a bit much for me. Not complaining, I am sure that's they way they are meant to be. Just mentioning it because eof I had known before I would have asked for it to be served without any additional butter.
It was absolutely delicious though.

My only "complaint" is that the coffees are very much on the small side, 3 sips and you're done.

reviews.title: exdellent value,food and staff
reviews.text:
The best pancake I have ever been served, freshly cooked to order
Friendly staff, good coffee quick service, at very reasonable prices.
Was very busy at lunch time.
Very good dessert offer for the 65+ Customers.

reviews.title: Nice terrace, good food

Nice terrace at the harbour.
Very friendly service.

reviews.title: Wonderful location for great pancakes
reviews.text:
Excellent pancakes in a wonderful location right on the harbour side. 
The waitress who served us was a delight, very friendly, helpful and professional.

reviews.title: Highly recommended!
reviews.text: We met up with friends here for lunch without ever having been to Harlingen before and were delighted with the location - what a great view of the harbour! - the delicious pancakes and poffertjes and the friendly service. It’s a great place to go to.

reviews.title: Poffertjes convert
reviews.text:
Intriguing square glass construction in a prime spot on Harlingen's dockside which drew me in like a magnet.  I discerned all kinds of puddingy comfort food on major scale, and once inside the place was cheerfully clean and orderly with a vast menu ready on each table with every item easily identifiable.

I was determined to try some poffertjes, and the entry level (i.e. small) was is a dozen little doughy pillows covered in icing sugar and a melting wedge of butter; very indulgent and thoroughly enjoyable. How tempting it must be to enhance these little guys with even more variety of flavours, and then maybe next time have a crack at the range of pancakes or waffles which are also available. The menu really is quite comprehensive with all sorts of sweet and savoury variations. It's interesting seeing the guy in the middle of the room operating the bespoke contraptions to produce this stuff, and he certainly does an excellent job.

A good choice of hot/cold drinks, beers and wines are available too so you really can have a full blown three course meal of these doughy items if your batter mix tolerance is high.

The industrious young waitresses were also well on the ball and friendly, so the whole experience was really most enjoyable.

reviews.title: Great pannekoeken!
reviews.text: We go to this Poffertjes Kraam every time we go to Harlingen. The atmosphere is great and the staf is very friendly.

reviews.title: Try to eat JUST ONE poffertje here... Can't be done!
reviews.text:
Before reviewing this to you, my dear foreigner, here's what's probably on your 'must eat' list when in Holland, or should be:

- Herring (raw, salted and sure to make you question your choices in life when it comes to foreign food)

- Kroket (blister inducing hot minced meat, needs a beer and mustard to enjoy fully. And cool down time. Lots. If not, send it back, it's not fried well.)

- Bitterballen (ball shaped kroket, yet smaller, same blistering of the mouth. Also needs beer, not coffee)

- Drop (Lickorize, in more flavours and sizes you would believe to be sane. Prepare to overdose and pop some veins & valves if going for the double salty ones)

- Stroopwafels (These should be in the logo of any Diabetes Association. Don't buy at the supermarket, go for the freshly baked ones on the market. Buy new clothes afterwards)

- Patatje kapsalon (Hairdressers' fries. Great taste! Eat blindfolded, because, well visually, the name reflects the resemblance of the product with the floors at said profession.)

- Shrooms (just don't. really. You can't fly, trust me.)

- POFFERTJES! 
There we go! Pronounced 'Pover chuzz' and if you start eating them with butter and powdered sugar, make sure no one minds you becoming XXXL. For our American friends: you'll be just fine.
So, if by some weird coincidence you find yourself at this lovely place in Harlingen, you could go for a lot of awesome different (yet slightly expensive) dishes, but the thing you really want are these tiny bloated sugary greased pancakes. By the dozen. Eat slowly. Enjoy. Look around at the nice harbour, those pretty ships and the happy faces of people around you eating 'poffertjes' in Harlingen. Ignore the screaming guy diving into the water next to the terrace. Probably had a 'kroket'.

reviews.title: Family lunch suitable for children
reviews.text:
We did a day trip to Harlingen without prior planing. After strolling around it was time for lunch and as we were close to the waterside and ready for pancake and other dutch sweets we ended up in this place by chance.
Our daughter loved it as they have got a kids corner will lots of toys to play, kept here busy. You can sit inside, outside or upstairs where is a room for groups.
The menu is mainly based on pancakes, however, we do talk sweet as well as saulty. As we were up for lunch we took the saulty options, basically like pizza just a different taste. Was all fresh and also the meat and fish quality was good. Beer was fine as well and it was filling nobody left with an empty stomach. Also shared the sweet dessert, was freshly prepared. Price was more than reasonable, especially in this location with the nice view on the boats.

reviews.title: A superb restaurant and dog friendly.
reviews.text: On a recent visit to Harlingen we spotted this restaurant on the waterfront, it was on an evening and they were just closing! So the next day we headed there with our dog and had brunch. The staff were very friendly and spoke good English. Food was excellent and lots of it, food arrived quickly and we sat in sun for longer than we intended savoring the meal. Will definitely go back.

reviews.title: Great place to sit in the sun
reviews.text:
It an excellent location to sit, enjoy the sun, have something to eat and drink. But only if you don't mind waiting. Even though I have been here on various occasions, it's the same every time. They are very slow and it takes forever for them to clean up. 
I also think it is pretty expensive, so I like baking my own 'poffertjes' more then getting them at the 'Poffertjeskraam'. But if you want to go out, sit in the sun, enjoy the boats sail by, eat the Dutch tiny pancakes and you're not in a hurry... You should definitely give this a try.

reviews.title: simple food but tasty and friendly. nice location too
reviews.text: many varieties of Poffertjes an Pannenkoeken (pancakes) served in a modern building at a great location overlooking the harbor. We had lunch and were pleased with the food, service, location and price.We left in a happy state of mind.

reviews.title: Pancakes to delight and satisfy
reviews.text:
He: has always ordered the spek & appel pancake. Sweet, salty, fruity and savory all in one. 
She: has ordered different sweet pancakes each time. 
This trip a really nice group of Belgian motorcyclists on tour pulled in and chatted with each other. A friendly, jovial group that knows what's important.  Close to the harbor, the ferry, and the train station, with a large terrace to sit in the sunshine, if you're lucky. We were.

We are repeat visitors. :)

reviews.title: Nice experience
reviews.text: Great views, tasty food, kid-friendly, good service, beautiful terrace right on the water. What else could you want?!?

reviews.title: Real Dutch food
reviews.text: This is a real Dutch treat with 70 different pancakes!!! Also serves poffertjes and waffers. Together with a view on the harbor of Harlingen where you can see sailing ships and fisher boats enter

reviews.title: Depressing snack experience
reviews.text: We to this restaurant as it looked as a real upmarket nice little specially restaurant. However inside is became more and more apparent that this little jont was an ever going old that never had the change to renew. The old fashioned famous Dutch were never renewed. Instead they were industrialised by a 'new' pouring machine. Pathetic while depressing to see. The staff was the regular unexperienced student staff that did not had the flair that could had made this poffertjes kraam to nice little spot in the Harlinger harbour.

reviews.title: Great location to watch ships and enjoy good Dutch food!
reviews.text: We loved our visit to Harlinger Poffertjeskraam on our first day being in Harlingen as it provided an opportunity to watch the harbor, that had lots of boat action, and enjoy a great Dutch meal. The menu was very extensive so I asked our waitress her recommendation - she pointed out a tuna pannekucken that ended up being amazing. I'm used to eating sweeter Dutch pancakes, so this was not only novel, but was delicious, simple and very healthy. We also enjoyed some great coffee drinks!

reviews.title: Great place we stumbled upon!
reviews.text: We took the train to Harlingen while in The Netherlands on a trip from the US.  We stumbled upon this restaurant after walking through the harbor on a cold morning.  We are so glad we circled back to this spotlessly clean (no, really, the nice lady who helped us was subtly cleaning all around the restaurant while we ate) and delicious spot was the perfect fix we needed to gain more energy.  My mom thought the pancakes reminded her of those she ate as a child.  We had hot chocolate, a butter and sugar pancake and a ham pancake.

reviews.title: Nice restaurant on the shore of the Waddenzee
reviews.text:
We were looking for a place on Waddenzee to stop for couple of hours to watch a football match over Internet, so we found this restaurant, made a call and they confirmed that they do provide free Wi-Fi connection.
Wi-Fi worked well. Food was tasty. Beer was good. Location is just great - right in the harbour of Harlingen. Few steps from the see and old town of Harlingen. Had a nice walk after the match.

reviews.title: Delicious food, great location, what's not to like?
reviews.text: Stopped in here after a long bike ride and ended up enjoying a delicious pannenkoek out on the patio in the sun. The staff were friendly, attentive, and easily adapted to my lack of Dutch. I've eaten at a number of pannenkoek places in the Netherlands and this was easily the best one I've had so far!

reviews.title: Yummy pancakes and beautiful location
reviews.text: During a recent visit to Harlingen we decided to have dinner at this 'poffertjeskraam'.  The weather was beautiful and there was lots of outside seating with a great view of the old harbor.  The service was quick and courteous.   This restaurant offers 'poffertjes' (tiny pancakes), Belgian waffles and Dutch pancakes.  The pancake menu is impressive.  I had a pancake with cheese, bacon, egg and onion.  A delicious pancake, especially after adding a healthy helping of 'stroop' (syrup - really, try it, it's very good)  We look forward to stopping here again for a tasty meal for a decent price and a lovely view.

reviews.text: nice eaterie, decent prices, pleasant surroundings
